ear tenure spanning the company's early growth into one of New England's leading insurers. He simultaneously served as president of the Hartford Bank from 1819 to 1828."}],"former_ids":[],"career":[],"is_placeholder":false,"slug":"nathaniel-terry-1768"},"HD1331":{"id":"HD1331","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":5,"hooker_talcott_convergence":true},"parents":{"father_id":"T00387","mother_id":"H00362"},"tags":["hooker_talcott_descent"],"sources":[{"entry":"863","label":"Edward Hooker 1909"}],"birth":{"year":1774,"month":1,"day":17,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1841,"month":10,"day":26,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00421","children_ids":["HD1345","HD1346","HD1347","HD1348","HD1349","HD1350","HD1351","HD1352"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1798,"date_month":3,"date_day":14,"location_city":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut"}],"gender":"female","artworks":["ART006"],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"header":"Mother of an author and a Union general","body":"Catherine Wadsworth married Nathaniel Terry, one of Hartford's most prominent citizens, in 1798. The Hooker-Talcott blood that ran through her passed to her grandchildren: Rose Terry Cooke became one of New England's most celebrated regional authors, and Gen. Alfred Howe Terry led the Union assault on Fort Wagner and later commanded the Department of the Dakotas — present at the aftermath of the Little Bighorn. Catherine never lived to see either of them distinguish themselves; she died in 1841.","number":1,"category":"family"}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM056"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Catherine Wadsworth Terry","first_name":"Catherine","last_name":"Terry","maiden_name":"Wadsworth","married_names":["Terry"],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777484083/catherineterry_gl7mvk.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"former_ids":[],"education":[],"career":[],"is_placeholder":false,"slug":"catherine-terry-1774"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{"INST114":{"id":"INST114","primary_name":"United States Naval Academy","name":"United States Naval Academy","alt_names":["Annapolis"],"type":"service academy","founding_year":1845,"location":{"city":"Annapolis","county":"Anne Arundel","state":"Maryland","country":"United States"},"primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Naval_Academy","wikipedia_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Naval_Academy","primary_persons":[],"hooker_connected_people":["TD0141","TD0150","HD0880","HD1206","HD2382","HD2965","HD2966","HD2967","HD2968","HD3127","T01869","T01840","I00271","T01876","HD3335","I00300","TD0157","I00479","HD4101","HD4122","TD0242","I01138"],"person_ids":["X00855","X02014","X02091","X02359"],"related_institutions":[],"related_landmarks":[],"tags":[],"sources":[],"notes":"Founded 1845 at Annapolis Maryland. Hooker-tree connections through Adm. George Dewey (TD0141, Acting Midshipman September 23, 1854, graduated June 18, 1858 fifth of fourteen; instructor 1868-1870; commanded USS Constitution as training ship 1867-1870; laid Memorial Chapel cornerstone June 1904) and his nephew Cdr. Theodore Gibbs Dewey (TD0150, graduate). Dewey Hall and Dewey Field at the Academy named for the Admiral. Significant beneficiary of George Goodwin Dewey's 1963 estate."}},"crossConnections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"HD1364","link_text":"Gen. Alfred Howe Terry","display_label":"First cousin; both Civil War officers leading the charge","